<h2 id="overview">Overview: Two Different Philosophies</h2>

I've used both platforms extensively. ConvertKit runs the OperatorStack newsletter. AWeber handles email for venue-facing communications in our operation. Both deliver emails reliably. The differences come down to philosophy.

<p><strong>ConvertKit</strong> is built for creators and content operators. Tag-based subscribers, visual automation builder, clean modern interface, generous free tier. It prioritizes the operator who's building an audience and running automated sequences.</p>

<p><strong>AWeber</strong> is built for reliability and longevity. 25+ years of infrastructure, battle-tested deliverability, straightforward pricing. It prioritizes operators who want email that works without constant attention.</p>

Both are dramatically better than Mailchimp for deliverability. The choice between them is about preference, not quality.

