<p><strong>AWeber is consistently cheaper</strong> at every subscriber tier. The gap is most significant at smaller list sizes (AWeber is nearly half the price at 500 subscribers) and narrows as you scale. At 50,000+ subscribers, the difference is modest.</p>

<p><strong>Pricing stability:</strong> AWeber's pricing is transparent and predictable. ConvertKit has historically been transparent as well, though they've adjusted tiers and pricing more frequently. AWeber's 25-year track record of pricing stability is a genuine differentiator for operators who plan long-term.</p>

<h2 id="free-tiers">Free Tiers: ConvertKit Wins on Generosity</h2>

<p><strong>ConvertKit's free tier</strong> supports up to 10,000 subscribers with basic features: forms, landing pages, broadcasts, and one email sequence. You can run a meaningful email operation for months on the free plan before needing to upgrade.</p>

<p><strong>AWeber's free tier</strong> supports up to 500 subscribers with basic features: one list, landing pages, email templates, and basic automation. Functional for getting started, but you'll hit the limit much faster.</p>

<p><strong>For new operators:</strong> ConvertKit's free tier is the better starting point. Build your list to 1,000-5,000 subscribers without paying anything, then evaluate whether ConvertKit's features justify the higher price or whether AWeber's reliability and lower pricing better serve your needs at that point.</p>

<h2 id="affiliate">Affiliate Programs: AWeber Wins Significantly</h2>


<p><strong>AWeber: 50% lifetime recurring.</strong> For every customer you refer, you earn 50% of their monthly subscription for as long as they remain a customer. A customer paying $30/mo earns you $15/mo -- forever.</p>

<p><strong>ConvertKit: 30% lifetime recurring.</strong> Same model, lower percentage. A customer paying $29/mo earns you $8.70/mo forever.</p>

<p><strong>The economics:</strong> If you refer 50 customers averaging $30/mo:</p>
<ul>
  <li>AWeber: 50 × $15 = $750/mo recurring</li>
  <li>ConvertKit: 50 × $8.70 = $435/mo recurring</li>
</ul>

That's a $315/mo difference at 50 referrals. For operators who build significant affiliate income through their content, AWeber's program is substantially more generous.

Both programs are genuinely lifetime -- there's no cap, no expiration, and commissions continue for as long as the referred customer pays. This model creates meaningful passive income for content operators over time.

